However, the Lightness value in HSL is calculated by this formula:
Lightness(L) = ( (Max(R,G,B) - Min(R,G,B)) / (Max(R,G,B) + Min(R,G,B)) ) * 100
where R, G and B are the red, green and blue components of the hex color in the integer form (e.g. 255 for the hex code #178e0b).

So, Lightness(L) = ( (143 - 34 )/ (143 + 34 ) ) * 100 = 94.236 or rounded to the nearest integer: 94
